<HL>
   International Brief -- NEC Corp.:
   Pretax Earnings for Year
   Rose 31% to Record Level
</HL>
<DATE>
05/29/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10
</SO>
<CO>
   NIPNY
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
COMPUTERS AND INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (CPR)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEC Corp., a leading Japanese maker of computers and other
information equipment, said its consolidated pretax earnings
for the year ended March 31 climbed 31% to a record 173.74
billion yen ($1.15 billion) from 132.19 billion yen a year
earlier.
   Net income rose 32% to 85.22 billion yen, or 56.08 yen a
share, from 64.48 billion yen, or 43.18 yen a share. Sales
rose 12% to 3.444 trillion yen from 3.082 trillion yen.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   NEC's unconsolidated results were equally strong. Pretax
earnings rose 30% to 133.24 billion yen from 102.14 billion
yen. Unconsolidated net jumped 35% to 74.89 billion yen, or
49.29 yen a share, from 55.34 billion yen, or 37.05 yen a
share. Sales rose 8.6% to 2.76 trillion yen from 2.542
trillion yen. All of the results were records.
   Sales of computers and other electronic products -- NEC's
largest line, representing 44% of the total -- rose 13% to
1.506 trillion yen; communications equipment rose 9% to
875.02 billion yen; and electronic devices, including
semiconductors, rose 7.1% to 605.95 billion yen.
</TEXT>
