   His brother, Gary, finished 31st of 33 entries because of
problems with a wheel bearing. Only 15 cars were still
running at the end of the race, which was won by Arie
Luyendyk, a native of Sommelsdyk, the Netherlands, now living
in Scottsdale, Ariz.
