<CO>
   CANDA
</CO>
<IN>
STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)
</IN>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canadian steel production totaled 296,125 metric
tons in the week ended May 19, a 6.7% decline from 317,282
tons the previous week and a 4.5% decline from 309,983 tons a
year earlier, Statistics Canada, a federal agency, said.
   From Jan. 1 through May 19, production totaled 5,525,599
tons, an 11% drop from 6,225,071 tons a year earlier.
