<HL>
   International Brief -- Nippon Telegraph &amp; Telephone:
   Pretax Earnings Rose 17%
   For Year Ended March 31
</HL>
<DATE>
05/29/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10
</SO>
<CO>
   J.NTT
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
TELEPHONE SYSTEMS (TLS)
</IN>
<LP>
   Nippon Telegraph &amp; Telephone Corp. said its consolidated
pretax earnings in the fiscal year ended March 31 climbed 17%
to 510.55 billion yen ($3.38 billion) from 438.06 billion yen
in the previous fiscal year.
   Net profit earned by the parent company and its one
consolidated subsidiary, NTT Data Communications System
Corp., rose more, going up 23% to 273.75 billion yen from
222.96 billion.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Operating revenue came to 6.022 trillion yen, rising 3.1%
from 5.841 trillion yen and exceeding six trillion yen for
the first time.
   NTT plans to pay a dividend for the year of 6,000 yen,
including a special 1,000-yen dividend to commemorate the
100th anniversary of telephone service in Japan. Last fiscal
year, the company paid a dividend of 5,000 yen.
</TEXT>
